<P>
It is appalling enough to know that in 1989, we would have a need for a "Miss 
Black America Pageant," but it is an extra slap in the face when the broadcast 
is plagued with audio problems. The entire show was the pits. 
</P>
<P>
Madelon Washington, Whittier 
</P>
