60th-birthday party for Cole Porter, right, in May, 1953, guests included, from 
left, Sid Luft, Judy Garland's husband; agent Peter Sabiston; Rocky Cooper, 
wife of Gary Cooper; actresses Dorothy Dandridge, Merle Oberon and Judy 
Garland. Says Howard: "What I remember best about the party was Richard Burton, 
after a few drinks, kissingeverybody, including Clifton Webb. Personally, I 
don't think Clifton minded that a bit." Atthe time, she recalls, "life was 
getting to be one party after another. It was too much, so I left town for a 
year and a half. When I came back I said, 'God, where is everybody?' " ; Photo, 
