'40s, Hollywood's croquet fever touched off what Jean Howard describes as a 
party "that lasted three years." In the midst of the craze, movie-industry 
types were challenged to an East Coast versus West Coast playoff. Joseph 
Cotten, above, was rooting for the West team at Ric-Su-Dar in Palm Springs. At 
left, Cesar Romero, left, and Tyrone Power discuss strategy. Jean Howard 
</P>
