<P>
EASTERN EUROPE AND GERMANY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
In view of the discussions currently taking place over the dollar amount to be 
given to Poland, and the statement by Lech Walesa that Poland does not want the 
entire sum in dollars, but would like to see foreign businesses invest in his 
country, it occurs to me that there is an enormous untapped source of private 
funds in this country. I refer to those people of Polish background who send 
money to relatives in Poland. 
</P>
<P>
I suggest that emergency legislation be passed enabling such donations to be 
deducted from one's income tax as a legitimate expense. It is difficult enough 
to support one's own family in this country but to support one's relatives in 
Poland, as many do, is a double burden. 
</P>
<P>
