<HEADLINE>
<P>
BALLOON PAYMENT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
I was appalled to see the photo in the (Sept. 10) Travel Section of the cruise 
ship releasing a cloud of balloons over the sea. Someone in the cruise business 
needs to realize that those deflated balloons look like food to sea birds and 
animals and, after being swallowed, can block their stomachs. Starvation 
results. 
</P>
<P>
There have to be other ways to create a celebratory atmosphere which won't 
endanger the environment in which these creatures live and whose very existence 
heightens the enjoyment of the cruise goer. 
</P>
<P>
Let's hope those in charge of celebrations on the ships will search for less 
hazardous ways to send off a cruise. 
</P>
<P>
BERNICE VAN STEENBERGEN 
</P>
<P>
Long Beach 
</P>
</TEXT>
