<HEADLINE>
<P>
SAN BERNARDINO SALES DECLINE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
After a scalding spring, the market for new home sales in San Bernardino County 
cooled considerably during the summer, according to the Competitive Housing 
Market Report issued this month by the Meyers Group. 
</P>
<P>
Meyers' audit of all new residential projects in the county from June through 
August showed that sales totaled 2,482, which was 16.26% below the 2,974 units 
sold from March through May. 
</P>
<P>
As sales dropped during the quarter ending Aug. 31, detached-home prices 
increased slightly, with the base median price rising from $153,940 to 
$153,990. With limited numbers of condominiums and townhouses available, the 
base median price for attached housing remained at $101,990. 
</P>
<P>
The market flattened in part because San Bernardino draws buyers from Orange 
and Los Angeles counties, where housing has shifted from a seller's to a 
buyer's market, said Steve Johnson, vice president of a Meyers Group division 
based in Corona. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> LA092489-0064 </DOCNO>
<DOCID> 111544 </DOCID>
<DATE>
<P>
September 24, 1989, Sunday, Home Edition 
</P>
</DATE>
<SECTION>
<P>
Real Estate; Part 8; Page 16; Column 1; Real Estate Desk 
</P>
</SECTION>
<LENGTH>
<P>
408 words 
</P>
</LENGTH>
<HEADLINE>
<P>
GRAND OPENINGS; 
</P>
<P>
11 LUXURY HOMES AT BONITA PALMS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WayCon's Bonita Palms, a gated community in Bonita with 11 luxury homes, is 
celebrating its grand opening this weekend. 
</P>
<P>
The classic, two-level Mediterranean-style homes are situated on view lots on 
Annie Laurie Lane near Bonnie Brae in San Diego County. 
</P>
<P>
The project, a design of Robert Bowlus of Bowlus, Edinger &amp; Stark, features 
two floor plans ranging in size from 2,775 to 3,046 square feet. Prices range 
from $349,000 to $399,900. 
</P>
<P>
Features of the five-bedroom, three-bath homes include ceramic tile entries, 
marble accented wood-burning fireplaces, coffered ceilings, spacious pantries 
and oversized spa tubs. 
</P>
<P>
To reach the project, take Bonita Road east to Central Avenue, right to Bonnie 
Brae onto Annie Laurie Lane. Hours are from 11 a.m. to 6 p.m., Friday through 
Tuesday. 
</P>
<P>
</P>
<P>
Townhouse Models 
</P>
<P>
Three furnished models have been completed for the grand opening this weekend 
of the new residential community of Palm Crest. 
</P>
<P>
The new Lewis Homes townhouse development is located at the intersection of 
Rosecrans and Lemoli avenues in Hawthorne. It consists of 114 units with 2 or 3 
bedrooms, ranging in size from 1,166 to 1,589 square feet, as well as spacious 
balconies and two-car garages. 
</P>
<P>
The units, 32 of which have been reserved, are priced from $192,950 to 
$231,950. An anticipated $100 homeowners' monthly fee will be set for 
maintenance of common areas that include a swimming pool and spa. 
</P>
<P>
</P>
<P>
Laguna Niguel Preview 
</P>
<P>
Three Laguna Niguel projects built by S&amp;S Construction Co. are previewing 
model homes. 
</P>
<P>
Village Niguel Gardens, a gated condominium community, 28 of 313 units, offers 
four two-story plans with 3 bedrooms and 2 1/2 baths. Units are priced from 
$219,500 to $295,000. They include attached garages and one and two fireplaces. 
A recreation center at the site includes a pool and spa. 
</P>
<P>
Laguna Crest Homes, 42 of 138 1-2-story detached residences, have five floor 
plans with up to 4 bedrooms and 3 baths. Prices range from $269,500 to 
$389,500. 
</P>
<P>
Both projects can be reached from the La Paz Road exit of Interstate 5. 
</P>
<P>
Laguna Crest Estates 36 of 102 detached homes, with five floor plans, have 4 
bedrooms and 3 baths. They have two- or three-car garages, two or three 
fireplaces and range in price from $360,500 to $470,500. Reached from Crown 
Valley Parkway exit of Interstate 5. 
</P>
<P>
The developments are part of S&amp;S's 1,200-acre Country Village 
master-planned community. All models are open 10 a.m. to 6 p.m. daily. 
</P>
</TEXT>
