<HEADLINE>
<P>
'INDUSTRIOUSNESS' OF SANTA MONICA 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The first page of Sunday's (Sept. 17) Westside section reported on the 
industriousness of Santa Monica officials. They are very busy indeed -- busy 
attempting to destroy Los Angeles residential neighborhoods. They will reap the 
monetary benefits of an expanded Santa Monica Airport, while Los Angeles 
residents bear the brunt of the increased traffic. 
</P>
<P>
They also have been working to ram a light rail line through along Exposition 
Boulevard. It would go through commercial property in Santa Monica and through 
lovely residential areas in Los Angeles. 
</P>
<P>
Where will they strike next? 
</P>
<P>
ESTELLE EISLER 
</P>
<P>
Rancho Park 
</P>
</TEXT>
