<DOCNO> LA092489-0074 </DOCNO>
<DOCID> 111572 </DOCID>
<DATE>
<P>
September 24, 1989, Sunday, Home Edition 
</P>
</DATE>
<SECTION>
<P>
San Gabriel Valley; Part 9; Page 5; Column 1 
</P>
</SECTION>
<GRAPHIC>
<P>
Photo, New Home for the Homeless Union Station in Pasadena shows its heart on 
its sleeve by displaying on its walls some of the people it serves. The new 
building, which is scheduled to open in October, is designed to feed 225 each 
day and provide up to 56 beds a night in addition to offering a wide variety of 
social services. LOU MACK / Los Angeles Times 
</P>
</GRAPHIC>
