<HEADLINE>
<P>
THE MOVIE CHART 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By David Pecchia 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Films now going into production: 
</P>
<P>
The Comfort of Strangers (Erre/Sovereign). Shooting in Italy. Christopher 
Walken, Natasha Richardson, Rupert Everett and Helen Mirren star in this Paul 
Schrader-directed, Harold Pinter-scripted erotic thriller following an English 
couple on vacation in Venice. Producer Angelo Rizzoli. Distributor Sovereign. 
</P>
<P>
Kabukiman (Troma/Namco/Gaga). Shooting in New York. This action adventure 
concerns a NYC police detective who is somehow transformed into a 
crime-fighting Kabuki persona. Executive producer Masaya Kakamura. Producers 
Lloyd Kaufman and Michael Herz. Directors Herz and Kaufman. Screenwriter 
Kaufman, Andrew Osborne and Jeffrey W. Sass. Stars Rick Gianasi, Susan Byun and 
Noble Lee Lester. Distributor Troma. 
</P>
<P>
Love Supreme (40 Acres &amp; A Mule). Shooting in NYC. "Do the Right Thing's" 
Spike Lee produces/directs/scripts this one starring Denzel Washington and 
himself, among others. It's a tale of a jazz musician who must make some hard 
decisions regarding his musical life versus his romantic life. Also stars Ossie 
Davis, Giancarlo Esposito, Ruben Blades and John Turturro. Distributor 
Universal. Summer release. 
</P>
<P>
Mermaids (Orion). Shooting in Boston. Cher portrays a free-spirited mom to her 
sensitive, quiet daughter Winona Ryder, as the latter seeks to establish her 
own identity. Producers Patrick Palmer, Wally Nicita and Lauren Lloyd. Director 
Frank Oz. Screenwriter June Roberts. 
</P>
<P>
The Sheltering Sky (Film Trustees). Shooting in Algeria, Morocco, Niger and 
Rome. Debra Winger and John Malkovich star in this endeavor from director 
Bernardo Bertolucci, producer Jeremy Thomas and screenwriter Mark Peploe, who 
triumphed with "The Last Emperor." It's based on Paul Bowles' classic novel of 
the intimate relationships between three people in postwar Northern Africa. 
Also stars Campbell Scott (George C. and Colleen Dewhurst's son). Distributor 
Warner Bros. David Pecchia 
</P>
</TEXT>
