<HEADLINE>
<P>
ALLA BREVE:: FLOTOW: "MARTHA." LUCIA POPP, DORIS SOFFEL, SIEGFRIED JERUSALEM, 
SIGMUND NIMSGERN, KARL RIDDERBUSCH; CHORUS OF THE BAVARIAN RADIO; MUNICH RADIO 
ORCHESTRA CONDUCTED BY HEINZ WALLBERG. EURODISC 7789-2-RG (TWO COMPACT DISCS). 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By ALLAN ULRICH 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Flotow's 1847 comedy about life among England's pampered rich receives a 
performance that infuses new blood into its faded charms. The cast and Wallberg 
strike an appealing balance between theatrical vivacity and stylistic 
refinement. In 1977, when the recording sessions were held, the microphones 
caught Popp and Jerusalem in pristine estate. Her delectable Lady Harriet and 
his Mickleford abound in sweetness and finesse. The digital remastering gives 
no cause for complaint. At mid-price, this is a "Martha" worth savoring. ALLAN 
ULRICH 
</P>
