<HEADLINE>
<P>
CASTING JEWISH ACTORS AS JEWISH CHARACTERS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
What I said in a telephone interview for Willens' article was that the 
Hollywood moguls used to anglicize the names of their stars, not that they 
changed their own names, as was incorrectly reported. 
</P>
<P>
Today, many celebrities apparently keep their surnames, but the television 
industry casts them with non-Jewish names. 
</P>
<P>
I asked Willens why couldn't Jack Klugman have been cast as Dr. Shapiro instead 
of as Dr. Quincy? How about Lt. Goldberg for Peter Falk instead of Columbo? 
</P>
<P>
The TV networks have never, to the best of my knowledge, made a Jew as a Jew 
the hero in a dramatic series. Supporting roles, yes, but not leading roles. 
</P>
<P>
HARVEY B. SCHECHTER 
</P>
<P>
Western States Director 
</P>
<P>
Anti-Defamation League 
</P>
<P>
Los Angeles 
</P>
