</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Yolanda Krell's letter (Sept. 17) regarding the change at KFAC and Los Angeles' 
alleged lack of sophistication and culture was irritating in its 
simple-mindedness. 
</P>
<P>
As a longtime resident and lover of Los Angeles, I'm tired of the L.A. bashers 
who complain about the dearth of culture in our city. Since when is classical 
music the only source of "culture"? 
</P>
<P>
Los Angeles is a thriving city for the arts, and home to many respected 
artists, musicians, writers, film makers, etc. 
</P>
