<HEADLINE>
<P>
CHURCH'S SPIRE AND MEANING OF RELIGION 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Re the Crystal Cathedral's plans to add a $5.5-million stainless steel spire 
because the Rev. Robert Schuller "always felt that all great cathedrals have 
spires": 
</P>
<P>
First, I'd like to refer him to Matthew 6: "And when thou prayest, thou shalt 
not be as the hypocrites are, for they love to pray in the corners of the 
streets, that they may be seen of men. Lay not up for yourselves treasures upon 
earth . . . but in heaven . . . for there will be your heart." 
</P>
<P>
Next, I'd like to refer him to my banker. He's good for 9% on deposits of this 
size. That works out to a modest $495,000 per year in interest -- tax free for 
Schuller -- and no small beginning for any number of projects that could 
benefit Orange County's needy. 
</P>
<P>
Come back to earth, reverend. God knows, we could use the help. 
</P>
<P>
S. MENNING 
</P>
<P>
Costa Mesa 
