<P>
NEWSWIRE: FERRY SCORES 25, LEADS ITALIAN TEAM TO WIN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Danny Ferry scored 25 points, and former Boston Celtic Brian Shaw added 19 as 
Messaggero Roma beat Vismara Cantu, 90-86, in an Italian Basketball League 
opener Saturday at Cantu, Italy. 
</P>
<P>
Ferry, the No. 2 pick -- by the Clippers -- in the 1989 NBA draft, scored three 
of his points after Messaggero fell behind, 86-85, with less than two minutes 
left -- after leading by 19 points earlier. 
</P>
<P>
Shaw added two points in the final seconds as a partisan crowd of 3,300 booed 
and whistled at the U.S. stars. 
</P>
</TEXT>
