<P>
HANAUER WINS HYDROPLANE RACE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By AP 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
LAS VEGAS 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Chip Hanauer of Seattle drove Circus Circus to a course-record speed of 125.977 
m.p.h. and scored his 30th victory Saturday in the Budweiser Las Vegas Silver 
Cup unlimited hydroplane race on Lake Mead. 
</P>
<P>
Hanauer, who won his fourth national driving championship, beat Tom D'Eath in 
Miss Budweiser and in the process broke D'Eath's course mark of 121.957 m.p.h. 
set last year. 
</P>
