<HEADLINE>
<P>
FIRE CAUSES $500,000 DAMAGE TO GLENDALE STORE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Glendale Fire Department officials were investigating the cause of a fire that 
caused $500,000 in damage to a furniture store early Saturday, authorities 
said. 
</P>
<P>
No one was injured in the blaze, which broke out about 7:20 a.m. at Swanson's 
Furniture Store on the 2600 block of Honolulu Avenue, spokesman Tom Magallanes 
said. The blaze continued for 15 minutes before firefighters extinguished it, 
he said. 
</P>
<P>
About $300,000 in damage was done to the building and about $200,000 to 
contents, he said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
