<HEADLINE>
<P>
SAN PEDRO SPORTSWALK TO HONOR 4 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Kevin Lindsey 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The San Pedro Sportswalk announced its inductees for 1989 to a small invited 
group Thursday aboard the yacht Angelina II, cruising around Los Angeles 
Harbor. The inductees are Jerry West, general manager of the Los Angeles 
Lakers, baseball greats Roy Campanella and Jackie Robinson, and former world 
lightweight boxing champion Mando Ramos. 
</P>
<P>
The Sportswalk, founded in 1978 by the San Pedro Peninsula Chamber of Commerce, 
honors outstanding sports figures with Los Angeles connections. They are 
selected by a committee of sports media representatives and civic leaders. 
</P>
<P>
The bronze plaques will be placed in the sidewalks of San Pedro's Beacon Street 
Redevelopment District. The unveiling ceremony will take place at 10:30 a.m. 
Oct. 23 at the intersection of Harbor Boulevard and 6th Street. 
</P>
<P>
The winner of the Trani Sportswalk Award for 1989 was also announced: Ray 
Martinez, a San Pedro native, who was honored for his 34 years as a youth 
leader and executive leader of the San Pedro Boys Club. Kevin Lindsey 
</P>
</TEXT>
</DOC>
