<HEADLINE>
<P>
HIGH SCHOOL ROUNDUP; 
</P>
<P>
GIRLS' VOLLEYBALL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Royal d. Agoura, 15-1, 15-12 -- Royal finished undefeated in its own tournament 
by soundly beating Agoura in the final at Royal. 
</P>
<P>
Beth Kohs had seven kills and teammate Wende Brown added six for Royal in the 
final. 
</P>
<P>
In the semifinal round Saturday morning, Royal defeated Simi Valley, 15-2, 
15-11. 
</P>
<P>
Kohl, Alison Bantel and Michelle Pagan of Royal made the all-tournament team. 
Agoura's Noel Hagenberger and Christy Jannsen also were selected to the team. 
</P>
<P>
In the consolation final, Buena defeated Simi Valley, 15-5. 
</P>
<P>
Cleveland d. Huntington Park, 15-13 -- Cleveland, after roaring through pool 
play without a loss, defeated Huntington Park to win the 12-team Venice 
Invitational at Venice High. 
</P>
<P>
Middle hitters Monica Martin and Michele Diana each had five kills in the final 
for the Cavaliers. 
</P>
<P>
Cleveland defeated Marshall in the semifinal round, 15-13. 
</P>
<P>
WATER POLO 
</P>
<P>
Buena Park 8, Royal 7 -- Terry Heller's shot with six seconds to play forged a 
7-7 tie for Royal but Buena Park answered with a half-court goal at the buzzer 
in a Villa Park tournament match. 
</P>
<P>
Royal (2-5), which lost to San Clemente, 11-7, earlier Saturday afternoon, 
finished 1-3 in the tournament. Senior Devon Hurst scored 21 of the 
Highlanders' 26 tournament goals. 
</P>
</TEXT>
