<HEADLINE>
<P>
SANTA MONICA SCORES FAST, ROLLS OVER HARBOR, 40-13 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By KEN BANKS 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Santa Monica College jumped on top of visiting Harbor College early Saturday 
night and cruised to an easy 40-13 non-conference win. 
</P>
<P>
The Corsairs scored on their first three possessions. The first came on a 
nine-yard pass from Jeff Barrett to Phillip Frazier, culminating an 85-yard 
drive. The second, a two-yard run by Charles McKinzie, capped a 78-yard drive. 
The point-after attempt failed, but Santa Monica took a 20-0 lead several 
minutes later when McKinzie's nine-yard run ended another 85-yard march. 
</P>
<P>
Harbor (1-1) got on the scoreboard just before the first half ended when 
running back Bill Harris reversed his field, turing a potential loss into a 
56-yard touchdown run. 
</P>
<P>
Consecutive Harbor turnovers enabled Santa Monica to blow the game wide open in 
the second half. The Corsairs recovered a fumble at the Harbor 13-yard line, 
then got a one-yard run by Frazier to increase their lead to 27-6. Then Adonias 
Lucero's interception set up a 10-yard pass from Jeff Barrett to Travis Moore 
to make it 33-6. 
</P>
<P>
Harbor's Corey Henry scored on a one-yard run to make the score 33-13 after 
three quarters. Santa Monica quarterback Ernie Soto capped the scoring with a 
27-yard touchdown pass to Byron Jackson. 
</P>
</TEXT>
