<HEADLINE>
<P>
HIGH SCHOOL FOOTBALL; 
</P>
<P>
RUCKER RUNS ROUGHSHOD OVER BELL-JEFF 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By GREG MEADE 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Sophomore Pathon Rucker's 15-yard scoring run with 1:22 remaining propelled 
Glendale High to a 28-21 nonleague win over Bell-Jeff on Saturday night at 
Burroughs High. 
</P>
<P>
Rucker, a tailback playing in his second varsity game, rushed for 237 yards and 
two touchdowns in 17 carries. Rucker also had an 88-yard kickoff return to set 
up a score. 
</P>
<P>
Bell-Jeff knotted the score, 21-21, in the third quarter on a 34-yard touchdown 
pass from Rod Chapman to Steve Szekely. 
</P>
<P>
Glendale (1-2) opened the scoring on a seven-yard run by Rucker, which capped a 
96-yard drive. The Guards came back to tie on a 32-yard run by Earl Matthews. 
</P>
<P>
Rucker returned the ensuing kickoff 88 yards to the eight-yard line and junior 
Kyiamo-Waki Jones scored from four yards. Bell-Jeff again tied the score on an 
11-yard scoring run by Alfred Silva after a 73-yard drive. 
</P>
<P>
Glendale led at the half, 21-14, after a 14-yard scoring strike from Eric 
Keisau to John Martell. GREG MEADE 
</P>
</TEXT>
