<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMUNITY COLLEGE FOOTBALL ROUNDUP 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By GERRY PRICE 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Citrus 27, Antelope Valley 10 -- Antelope Valley outgained Citrus, 346 total 
yards to 281, but committed seven turnovers in the Foothill League opener for 
both teams at Lancaster. 
</P>
<P>
Citrus (1-2) ran off 20 unanswered points after Antelope Valley (1-2) had taken 
a 3-0 lead on John Ford's 26-yard field goal. 
</P>
<P>
Antelope Valley running back Jerald Mitchell rushed for 63 yards in 17 carries 
and one touchdown. Quarterback Mike Dalley completed nine of 25 passes for 135 
yards but threw three interceptions. 
</P>
<P>
Backup quarterback Cole Speer also threw an interception and both quarterbacks 
each lost one fumble. GERRY PRICE 
</P>
