<HEADLINE>
<P>
COLLEGE ROUNDUP; 
</P>
<P>
NORTHRIDGE FALLS IN FINAL TO PORTLAND ST. 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Portland State, the defending Division II national women's volleyball champion, 
defeated Cal State Northridge for the second time in a week to win the Portland 
State tournament Saturday, this time by a score of 15-10, 13-15, 15-13, 15-8. 
</P>
<P>
Kathleen Dixon and Keira Middleton of Northridge were selected to the 
all-tournament team. 
</P>
<P>
In an earlier match, Northridge defeated Regis State of Colorado, 15-3, 15-5, 
15-9. 
</P>
<P>
In other women's volleyball matches: 
</P>
<P>
Pierce d. Glendale (Ariz.), 15-11 -- Outside hitter Anna Suarez had six kills 
and middle blocker Andrea Banducci added five as Pierce won the 12-team Cypress 
tournament at Cypress College. 
</P>
<P>
MEN'S SOCCER 
</P>
<P>
Occidental 3, Whittier 0 -- Aran Aleamoni scored three goals to lead the host 
Tigers in a Southern California Intercollegiate Athletic Conference soccer 
match. 
</P>
<P>
Aleamoni scored at the 22:40 and 30:42 marks of the first half and with 14 
minutes left in the match. 
</P>
<P>
Will Price assisted Aleamoni on the first and third goals and Jay Caba assisted 
on the second. 
</P>
<P>
Occidental is 1-3-2 overall and 1-0-2 in SCIAC play. Whittier is 1-2 in the 
SCIAC. 
</P>
<P>
Cal Lutheran 3, Redlands 0 -- Casey Pirih, Jesse Gallegos and Larry Gidley 
scored to boost the host Kingsmen (4-2) to their fourth consecutive 
nonconference victory. 
</P>
<P>
University of San Diego 2, CSUN 1 -- The Toreros (2-1) handed the Matadors 
(3-1-2) their first loss of the season in a Nevada Las Vegas tournament match. 
</P>
<P>
CROSS-COUNTRY 
</P>
<P>
Aztec Invitational: Cal State Northridge, led by an 18th-place finish by Sasha 
Vujic, placed 11th in the 36-team meet at San Diego's Balboa Park. CSUN was the 
highest-finishing Division II team in the field. 
</P>
<P>
Arizona's Marc Davis won the eight-kilometer race, finishing in 24 minutes, 48 
seconds. Vujic finished in 25:56. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<CORRECTION-DATE>
<P>
September 27, 1989, Wednesday, Valley Edition 
</P>
</CORRECTION-DATE>
<CORRECTION>
<P>
FOR THE RECORD 
</P>
<P>
CSUN volleyball -- A story in Sunday's edition stated incorrectly that the 
Portland State women's volleyball team won its own tournament after defeating 
Cal State Northridge in the Portland Tournament. Northridge did lose the match, 
but it was awarded the tournament championship on the basis of total points 
won. Northridge, Portland State and Regis (Colo.) College all finished the 
round-robin tournament with a record of 3-1. 
</P>
</CORRECTION>
