<HEADLINE>
<P>
MORSE HOLDS OFF VISTA IN FINAL MINUTE TO WIN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Vista High had the ball in Morse territory with a minute to go, but couldn't 
convert on fourth and one and Morse held on for a 22-20 nonleague victory 
Saturday. 
</P>
<P>
Morse took a 22-13 lead into halftime on two touchdowns from quarterback Teddy 
Lawrence, one a 20-yard run and the other an eight-yard pass. 
</P>
<P>
Ututofo Faime also scored for Morse, on a two-yard run in the second quarter. 
</P>
<P>
Vista then shut down Morse in the second half, but the Tigers had done their 
damage. 
</P>
<P>
Vista's only touchdown in the first half came on a 20-yard pass from Choo Choo 
Walker to Jose Castaneda. 
</P>
<P>
Castaneda scored on a three-yard run in the third quarter and fullback Ken 
Williams closed out the scoring with a fourth-quarter one-yard touchdown run. 
</P>
<P>
St. Augustine 33, Marian 0 -- The Saints (3-0) have outscored their opponents, 
110-12. 
</P>
<P>
Marian dropped to 0-3. 
</P>
<P>
Hunter Buckner opened the scoring with his sixth touchdown of the season, a 
three-yard run. 
</P>
<P>
The big story, however, was junior quarterback Chad Tomaskasoski, who was six 
of 14 for 106 yards with one touchdown pass and two touchdown runs. 
</P>
</TEXT>
