<HEADLINE>
<P>
MOST WANTED FRENCH CRIMINAL KILLS HIMSELF 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Reuters 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
LIEGE, Belgium 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Philippe Delaire, France's most wanted criminal, killed himself early Saturday 
after he and two accomplices, cornered by police on the roof of an apartment 
building, tossed part of $720,000 in ransom money to onlookers on the street 
below. 
</P>
<P>
A spokeswoman for the public prosecutor said Delaire, 28, appeared to have 
committed suicide just as police burst into a building in Droixhe, near Liege, 
where he had taken refuge with his two accomplices. She did not say how he 
died. 
</P>
<P>
Police said earlier that Delaire, known in the underworld as Beau Mec (Pretty 
Boy) because of his good looks, had died of head wounds in a hail of bullets 
after being cornered on the staircase of an apartment block. 
</P>
<P>
Delaire, who had broken out of at least four jails in France and Belgium 
including one jailbreak in Nice by helicopter, had held a woman and her two 
daughters in a suburban villa for six days. 
</P>
<P>
His two accomplices were arrested. one of them was shot and wounded by police 
when he threatened them with a hand grenade, the spokeswoman said. 
</P>
<P>
The three gunmen earlier released their hostages, Marie-Madeleine Bolland and 
daughters Francoise, 12, and Gaelle, 10, in exchange for the ransom and a 
getaway car. 
</P>
<P>
After zig-zagging around the Liege area and switching cars several times to 
throw off police, the gang headed for Delaire's hideout in Droixhe. But police 
already had it staked out. 
</P>
</TEXT>
