<HEADLINE>
<P>
CALM HOME SAVINGS ROBBER HANDS TELLER NOTE, WALKS OUT WITH CASH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Police are searching for a man who calmly handed a teller a note demanding 
money, then casually walked out of Home Savings of America in Fullerton with an 
undetermined amount of money Saturday morning. 
</P>
<P>
The apparently unarmed robber demanded the money about 11:20 a.m. at the branch 
at 1107 S. Harbor Blvd., Fullerton Police Sgt. Ron Gillett said. 
</P>
<P>
A handful of customers in the savings and loan at the time did not know a 
robbery had taken place, Gillett said. 
</P>
<P>
Employees said they did not see whether the man fled by foot or by car. 
</P>
</TEXT>
